# FX.6.3 (2026-05-04): explicit top-level pin for the ``anthropic`` SDK
# so the version is controlled here rather than left to whatever
# ``langchain-anthropic`` happens to resolve. Bumped from the previously
# transitive 0.95.0 to the latest stable 0.97.0. NOTE: the TODO entry
# said "1.x+ latest stable" but PyPI has no 1.x release of ``anthropic``
# (top of the stable line is 0.97.0 as of 2026-05-04 — the 1.x family
# the TODO author was thinking of is ``langchain-anthropic``, not the
# raw SDK). No code adaptation needed: the SDK surface we use
# (``anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=...)`` + ``client.messages.create()``
# + ``usage.input_tokens / output_tokens``) has been stable across the
# 0.85 → 0.97 range. ``langchain-anthropic==1.4.0`` declares
# ``anthropic<1.0.0,>=0.85.0`` so 0.97.0 is in-spec.
anthropic==0.97.0

