# --- I9/I10: Redis-backed rate limiting + multi-worker shared state ---
# FX.6.2 (2026-05-04): removed duplicate ``redis==7.4.0`` line — kept only
# the extras-form ``redis[hiredis]`` because pip resolves both lines to the
# same redis package, so the bare line was a no-op that just made the file
# look ambiguous. The extras form pulls in the C-accelerated ``hiredis``
# parser, which is what backend code actually needs at runtime.
redis[hiredis]==7.4.0

# --- C1: SSH remote runner (optional) ----------------------------------
# Only needed for cross-arch targets requiring paramiko-based remote
# execution. The module (backend/ssh_runner.py) lazy-imports paramiko
# and raises a clear error at call time if missing — so the system
# starts and runs fine without it. Install when you need SSH:
#   pip install paramiko
#
# FX.6.4 (2026-05-04): paramiko is NOT pinned here. Earlier revisions
# kept ``paramiko==4.0.0`` as a hard pin under this header, which made
# it land in ``requirements.txt`` (a "ghost" — present in the lockfile
# but the surrounding comment said it should be optional). The pin
# also dragged ``bcrypt`` into the runtime image purely for paramiko's
# own host-key handling — neither is used by any non-SSH code path.
# To install on a host that actually needs SSH:
#   ./backend/.venv/bin/pip install paramiko==4.0.0
# (test_ssh_runner.py uses ``pytest.importorskip('paramiko')`` so the
#  unit suite stays green without it; ssh_runner.py itself raises
#  RuntimeError with an actionable install hint at call time.)
